    "To achieve this, they train a reinforcement learning-based neural batch sampler to amplify the difference in loss curves between anomalous and non-anomalous regions.",
    "FCDD [35] is an unsupervised method that synthesizes abnormal samples for training the OCC model.",
    "This concept is transferable to other OCC methods.",
    "Venkataramanan et al. [42] propose a convolutional adversarial variational autoencoder (CAVGA) with guided attention that can be applied equally to cases with and without abnormal images.",
